sting\n(or expected) constraints from accelerators and astrophysics, combined with\ncosmological requirements, puts robust limits on the maximally possible nuclear\nscattering rate. In most regions of parameter space these are at least\ncompetitive with the best projected limits from currently planned direct\ndetection experiments.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 18 Sep 2019 18:00:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 18 Oct 2019 06:58:07 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 24 Mar 2020 15:17:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-22"}
